def lists_with_product_equal_n(circular_list):
    sublists = []
    size = len(circular_list)

    for i in range(size):
        product = 1
        sublist = []
        for j in range(size):
            index = (i + j) % size
            product *= circular_list[index]
            sublist.append(circular_list[index])
            if product == 29:
                sublists.append(sublist)
    return sublists
